# 📊 2. Impact vs Urgency Prioritization

Here’s how a PM would justify sequencing:

---

## 🔥 High Impact + High Urgency (Build First)

| Feature                | Why                   |
| ---------------------- | --------------------- |
| Project Recommendation | Drives activation     |
| Guided Project Mode    | Core value            |
| AI Assistance          | Prevents churn        |
| Basic Feedback         | Enables learning loop |

👉 These define **product-market fit**

---

## ⚡ High Impact + Medium Urgency

| Feature        | Why                     |
| -------------- | ----------------------- |
| Peer Feedback  | Builds real-world skill |
| Community Feed | Drives engagement       |
| Skill Graph    | Long-term value         |

---

## 🧪 Medium Impact + Low Urgency

| Feature      | Why                |
| ------------ | ------------------ |
| Gamification | Enhances retention |
| Dev Logs     | Social layer       |
| Idea Board   | Exploration        |

---

## 💤 Low Impact (Initially)

| Feature         | Why                        |
| --------------- | -------------------------- |
| Recruiter Layer | Needs scale + trust        |
| Certifications  | Doesn’t solve core problem |

